issue.title: Rewrite git-gud in go
issue.body:
# Feature
Rewrite git-gud in go. Features faster processing of StackExchange answers and ignoring common error messages such as 'not a git command' and 'empty commit message'

Fixes #1 

## Dependencies
- [gjson](https://github.com/tidwall/gjson)
- [html2text](https://github.com/jaytaylor/html2text)

## Building
```
go build -o gud git-gud.go
```

## Installation
Move `gud` to `/usr/local/bin` using
```
sudo mv <path to gud> /usr/local/bin
```

Apt repository coming soon

issue.title: Single word arguments in quotation marks throws error
issue.body: Using commands such as `commit -m "word"` will throw an error as the quotation marks haven't been escaped and/or parsed.
